<item>
            <title>[FELIX-5917] [Fwk security] Fix BundlePermission check for fragments</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5917</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With the current framework a fragment seems to require&lt;br/&gt;
(org.osgi.framework.BundlePermission &quot;*&quot; &quot;fragment&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
to attach to a host, instead of the expected and more restrictive&lt;br/&gt;
(org.osgi.framework.BundlePermission &quot;&amp;lt;host-symbolic-name&amp;gt;&quot; &quot;fragment&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have tested with Equinox as well, to make sure the provided symbolic name is correct etc., then it works as expected.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Framework 6.0.0 + Fwk security 2.6.0</environment>
        <key id="13181013">FELIX-5917</key>
